            "height": 1080,
            "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2021/04/Florida-Trans-Am-Shop-Burns--3.jpg"
          }
        ],
        "caption": "photo credit: Facebook"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Of the many cars saved from the fire was the only surviving Knight Rider KITT Super Pursuit Mode car created by Jay Orberg. While it’s sad that the other two cars were destroyed, another piece of history was preserved for future generations to appreciate.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Also suffering serious damage in the fire was the shop’s main offices. Also lost in the fire were a number of Trans Am memorabilia kept in the office. In a Facebook post, Trans Am Specialties of Florida said it would be able to get back to work soon after the cleanup process is over. Since the damage looks pretty bad, we’re not sure when that will be, but hopefully it’s sooner than later.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
